09/06/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Prime Minister Adrian Nastase and his Hungarian counterpart, Peter Medgyessy, met at the newly-opened border crossing at Urziceni-Vallaj on Friday (6 June).
They discussed issues related to bilateral co-operation, describing the new checkpoint as representing the will for closer and more open communication.
Also Friday, Ovidiu Musetescu, chairman of the Romanian privatisation authority APAPS paid a working visit to Hungary.
Musetescu met with government officials and corporate representatives, inviting them to participate in the privatisation of 80 large Romanian companies.
(ACT Media, Rompres - 09/06/03)
